Question: How to write csv file on the basis of Excel using java?: :I have spreadsheet with certain data. I would like to programmatically dump this to CSV file. How can I do this using java?
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Iterator.next
<<<code>>>: FileWriter fileWriter = new FileWriter("file.csv");
Iterator<String[]> data = yourData.iterator();
while(data.hasNext()){
    String[] line = data.next();
    fileWriter.append(String.join(",", line));
    fileWriter.append("\n");
}
fileWriter.flush();
fileWriter.close();
<<<explanation>>>: The next() method of the Iterator interface returns the next element in the iteration. This is a terminal operation.
Question: How can I read a file in Java?
